{
  "intro.line1": "I'm an artist based in Naarm / Melbourne, sculpting real-time systems into Visual Art, Interactive Art, audiovisual performance, lighting, and more. Primarily working and teaching in TouchDesigner.",
  "about.p1": "Nicholas Marriott is a creative technologist based in Naarm / Melbourne, b. 1999 in Aotearoa New Zealand. He works in real-time systems as a visual designer, performer, and exhibiting artist, across a variety of mediums.",
  "about.p2": "His visuals have featured on major stages and screens, including The xx's 2026 festival tour and a Grammy-winning music video for Nine Inch Nails, alongside commercial work for Nike and live performances at festivals including Pitch Music & Arts. His installation work extends these systems into physical space, most recently a large-scale reactive light environment for Chadstone. His practice has been profiled in It's Nice That and Rolling Stone.",
  "now.statement": "Seeking experimentation and collaborative artistic exploration through the use of real-time technology, especially in performance. Please don't hesitate to reach out if this is relevant to you!",
